WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:25.000
CHAPTER VII THROUGH XII.

00:33.400 --> 00:40.600
And the Lord said unto Noah, Come thou and all thy house into the ark, for thee have

00:40.600 --> 00:43.880
I seen righteous before me in this generation.

00:45.400 --> 00:54.980
Of every clean beast thou shalt take to thee by sevens, the male and his female, and of

00:54.980 --> 01:03.380
of fowls also of the air by sevens, the male and the female, to keep seed alive upon the

01:03.380 --> 01:04.900
face of all the earth.

01:05.660 --> 01:11.780
For yet seven days, and I will cause it to rain upon the earth forty days and forty nights,

01:12.280 --> 01:17.820
and every living substance that I have made will I destroy from off the face of the earth.

01:18.760 --> 01:22.780
And Noah did according unto all that the Lord commanded him.

01:23.610 --> 01:28.440
And Noah was six hundred years old when the flood of waters was upon the earth.

01:29.780 --> 01:36.100
And Noah went in, and his sons, and his wife, and his sons' wives with him, into the ark,

01:36.380 --> 01:38.460
because of the waters of the flood.

01:39.880 --> 01:45.560
Of clean beasts, and of beasts that are not clean, and of fowls, and of every thing that

01:45.560 --> 01:51.980
creepeth upon the earth, there went in two and two unto Noah into the ark, the male and

01:51.980 --> 01:54.840
the female, as God had commanded Noah.

01:56.640 --> 02:02.200
And it came to pass after seven days that the waters of the flood were upon the earth.

02:03.560 --> 02:08.820
In the six hundredth year of Noah's life, in the second month, the seventeenth day of

02:08.820 --> 02:14.820
the month, the same day were all the fountains of the great deep broken up, and the windows

02:14.820 --> 02:16.180
of heaven were opened.

02:16.980 --> 02:21.180
And the rain was upon the earth forty days and forty nights.

02:22.520 --> 02:29.400
In the selfsame day entered Noah, and Shem, and Ham, and Japeth, the sons of Noah, and

02:29.400 --> 02:36.060
Noah's wife, and the three wives of his sons with them, into the ark, they and every beast

02:36.060 --> 02:42.020
after his kind, and all the cattle after their kind, and every creeping thing that creepeth

02:42.020 --> 02:49.180
upon the earth after his kind, and every fowl after his kind, every bird of every sort.

02:50.000 --> 02:56.520
And they went in unto Noah into the ark two and two of all flesh wherein is the breath

02:56.520 --> 02:57.340
of life.

02:57.940 --> 03:04.540
And they that went in, went in male and female of all flesh, as God had commanded him, and

03:04.540 --> 03:05.940
the Lord shut him in.

03:06.780 --> 03:13.000
And the flood was forty days upon the earth, and the waters increased and bare up the ark,

03:13.360 --> 03:15.620
and it was lift up above the earth.

03:16.440 --> 03:22.200
And the waters prevailed and were increased greatly upon the earth, and the ark went upon

03:22.200 --> 03:23.540
the face of the waters.

03:24.320 --> 03:29.540
And the waters prevailed exceedingly upon the earth, and all the high hills that were

03:29.540 --> 03:31.640
under the whole heaven were covered.

03:32.860 --> 03:37.740
Fifteen cubits upward did the waters prevail, and the mountains were covered.

03:38.640 --> 03:45.320
And all flesh died that moved upon the earth, both of fowl and of cattle and of beast and

03:45.320 --> 03:51.820
of every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth and every man, all in whose nostrils

03:51.820 --> 03:56.520
was the breath of life, of all that was in the dry land, died.

03:57.420 --> 04:03.240
And every living substance was destroyed which was upon the face of the ground, both man

04:03.240 --> 04:08.720
and cattle and the creeping things and the fowl of the heaven, and they were destroyed

04:08.720 --> 04:14.660
from the earth, and Noah only remained alive and they that were with him in the ark.

04:15.700 --> 04:19.920
And the waters prevailed upon the earth and hundred and fifty days.

04:21.960 --> 04:23.160
CHAPTER VIII

04:23.160 --> 04:28.840
And God remembered Noah and every living thing and all the cattle that was with him in the

04:28.840 --> 04:34.300
ark, and God made a wind to pass over the earth and the waters assuaged.

04:35.000 --> 04:40.560
The fountains also of the deep and the windows of heaven were stopped and the rain from heaven

04:40.560 --> 04:47.140
was restrained, and the waters returned from off the earth continually, and after the end

04:47.140 --> 04:50.620
of the hundred and fifty days the waters were abated.

04:51.900 --> 04:56.980
And the ark rested in the seventh month on the seventeenth day of the month upon the

04:56.980 --> 04:58.300
mountains of Ararat.

04:59.320 --> 05:04.800
And the waters decreased continually until the tenth month, in the tenth month on the

05:04.800 --> 05:08.280
first day of the month were the tops of the mountains seen.

05:09.080 --> 05:14.820
And it came to pass at the end of forty days that Noah opened the window of the ark which

05:14.820 --> 05:21.460
he had made, and he sent forth a raven which went forth to and fro until the waters were

05:21.460 --> 05:23.280
dried up from off the earth.

05:24.480 --> 05:30.440
Also he sent forth a dove from him to see if the waters were abated from off the face

05:30.440 --> 05:31.220
of the ground.

05:31.820 --> 05:37.240
But the dove found no rest for the sole of her foot, and she returned under him into

05:37.240 --> 05:41.040
the ark, for the waters were on the face of the whole earth.

05:41.480 --> 05:47.200
Then he put forth his hand and took her and pulled her in unto him into the ark.

05:48.380 --> 05:55.020
And he stayed yet other seven days, and again he sent forth the dove out of the ark, and

05:55.020 --> 06:00.900
the dove came into him in the evening, and lo, in her mouth was an olive-leaf plucked

06:00.900 --> 06:05.580
off, so Noah knew that the waters were abated from off the earth.

06:06.260 --> 06:12.740
And he stayed yet other seven days, and sent forth the dove, which returned not again unto

06:12.740 --> 06:14.020
him any more.

06:15.280 --> 06:20.720
And it came to pass in the six hundredth and first year, in the first month, the first

06:20.720 --> 06:26.640
day of the month, the waters were dried up from off the earth, and Noah removed the covering

06:26.640 --> 06:31.460
of the ark, and looked, and behold, the face of the ground was dry.

06:32.300 --> 06:37.280
And in the second month, on the seventh and twentieth day of the month, was the earth

06:37.280 --> 06:37.800
dried.

06:39.220 --> 06:45.900
And God spake unto Noah, saying, Go forth of the ark thou and thy wife and thy sons

06:45.900 --> 06:48.080
and thy sons' wives with thee.

06:48.900 --> 06:55.000
Bring forth with thee every living thing that is with thee of all flesh, both of fowl and

06:55.000 --> 07:00.420
of cattle, and of every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth, that they may breed

07:00.420 --> 07:05.420
abundantly in the earth and be fruitful and multiply upon the earth.

07:06.620 --> 07:11.700
And Noah went forth and his sons and his wife and his sons' wives with him.

07:12.480 --> 07:18.380
Every beast, every creeping thing, and every fowl, and whatsoever creepeth upon the earth

07:18.380 --> 07:21.720
after their kinds, went forth out of the ark.

07:22.920 --> 07:28.960
And Noah builded an altar unto the Lord, and took of every clean beast and of every clean

07:28.960 --> 07:32.280
fowl, and offered burnt offerings on the altar.

07:33.140 --> 07:39.300
And the Lord smelled a sweet savor, and the Lord said in his heart, I will not again curse

07:39.300 --> 07:45.420
the ground any more for man's sake, for the imagination of man's heart is evil from his

07:45.420 --> 07:51.360
youth, neither will I again smite any more every thing living as I have done.

07:52.060 --> 07:58.940
While the earth remaineth seed-time and harvest and cold and heat and summer and winter and

07:58.940 --> 08:01.800
day and night shall not cease.

08:03.980 --> 08:05.180
CHAPTER IX

08:06.400 --> 08:13.000
And God blessed Noah and his sons and said unto them, Be fruitful and multiply and replenish

08:13.000 --> 08:18.820
the earth, and the fear of you and the dread of you shall be upon every beast of the earth,

08:19.020 --> 08:24.960
and upon every fowl of the air, upon all that moveth upon the earth, and upon all the fishes

08:24.960 --> 08:28.400
of the sea, into your hand are they delivered.

08:29.540 --> 08:35.040
Every moving thing that liveth shall be meat for you, even as the green herb have I given

08:35.040 --> 08:36.340
you all things.

08:37.080 --> 08:42.400
But flesh with the life thereof, which is the blood thereof, shall ye not eat.

08:42.960 --> 08:48.580
And surely your blood of your lives will I require, at the hand of every beast will I

08:48.580 --> 08:54.360
require it, and at the hand of man, at the hand of every man's brother will I require

08:54.360 --> 08:55.660
the life of man.

08:56.560 --> 09:02.960
Whoso shedeth man's blood, by man shall his blood be shed, for in the image of God made

09:02.960 --> 09:03.860
he man.

09:04.540 --> 09:11.460
And you, be ye fruitful and multiply, bring forth abundantly in the earth, and multiply

09:11.460 --> 09:12.220
therein.

09:13.400 --> 09:20.660
And God spake unto Noah and to his sons with him, saying, And I, behold, I establish my

09:20.660 --> 09:26.100
covenant with you, and with your seed after you, and with every living creature that is

09:26.100 --> 09:31.960
with you, of the fowl, of the cattle, and of every beast of the earth with you, from

09:31.960 --> 09:35.540
all that go out of the ark to every beast of the earth.

09:36.020 --> 09:41.920
And I will establish my covenant with you, neither shall all flesh be cut off any more

09:41.920 --> 09:47.740
by the waters of a flood, neither shall there be any more of flood to destroy the earth.

09:48.800 --> 09:55.180
And God said, This is the token of the covenant which I make between me and you, and every

09:55.180 --> 09:58.940
living creature that is with you, for perpetual generations.

09:59.420 --> 10:05.580
I do set my bow in the cloud, and it shall be for a token of a covenant between me and

10:05.580 --> 10:06.320
the earth.

10:06.940 --> 10:11.860
And it shall come to pass, when I bring a cloud over the earth, that the bow shall be

10:11.860 --> 10:18.880
cloud, and I will remember my covenant which is between me and you and every living creature

10:18.880 --> 10:25.120
of all flesh, and the waters shall no more become a flood to destroy all flesh.

10:25.940 --> 10:31.780
And the bow shall be in the cloud, and I will look upon it, that I may remember the everlasting

10:31.780 --> 10:37.520
covenant between God and every living creature of all flesh that is upon the earth.

10:38.380 --> 10:44.400
And God said unto Noah, This is the token of the covenant which I have established between

10:44.400 --> 10:47.340
me and all flesh that is upon the earth.

10:49.140 --> 10:55.260
And the sons of Noah that went forth of the ark were Shem and Ham and Japheth, and Ham

10:55.260 --> 10:56.820
is the father of Canaan.

10:57.920 --> 11:03.140
These were the three sons of Noah, and of them was the whole earth overspread.

11:03.800 --> 11:09.920
And Noah began to be an husbandman, and he planted a vineyard, and he drank of the wine,

11:10.040 --> 11:13.700
and was drunken, and he was uncovered within his tent.

11:14.420 --> 11:20.980
And Ham, the father of Canaan, saw the nakedness of his father, and told his two brethren without.

11:21.800 --> 11:27.740
And Shem and Japheth took a garment, and laid it upon both their shoulders, and went backward,

11:27.740 --> 11:33.220
and covered the nakedness of their father, and their faces were backward, and they saw

11:33.220 --> 11:35.280
not their father's nakedness.

11:36.460 --> 11:41.740
And Noah awoke from his wine, and knew what his younger son had done unto him.

11:42.220 --> 11:48.440
And he said, Cursed be Canaan, a servant of servants shall he be unto his brethren.

11:49.360 --> 11:54.840
And he said, Blessed be the Lord God of Shem, and Canaan shall be his servant.

11:55.640 --> 12:01.520
God shall enlarge Japheth, and he shall dwell in the tents of Shem, and Canaan shall be

12:01.520 --> 12:02.340
his servant.

12:03.900 --> 12:07.940
And Noah lived after the flood three hundred and fifty years.

12:08.580 --> 12:13.480
And all the days of Noah were nine hundred and fifty years, and he died.

12:16.580 --> 12:23.200
Now these are the generations of the sons of Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth, and unto

12:23.200 --> 12:25.780
them were sons born after the flood.

12:26.960 --> 12:34.340
The sons of Japheth, Gomer, and Magog, and Medai, and Javan, and Tubal, and Meshach,

12:34.580 --> 12:35.340
and Tyrus.

12:36.220 --> 12:40.980
And the sons of Gomer, Ashkenaz, and Riphoth, and Togarmah.

12:41.620 --> 12:47.300
And the sons of Javan, Elisha, and Tarshish, Kitim, and Dodenim.

12:48.080 --> 12:53.940
By these were the Isles of the Gentiles divided in their lands, every one after his tongue,

12:54.260 --> 12:56.820
after their families, in their nations.

12:58.240 --> 13:03.320
And the sons of Ham, Cush, and Misraim, and Foot, and Canaan.

13:04.300 --> 13:10.720
And the sons of Cush, Seba, and Havilah, and Sabta, and Rehema, and Sabtika.

13:11.400 --> 13:14.460
And the sons of Rehema, Sheba, and Dedan.

13:14.460 --> 13:22.520
And Cush begat Nimrod, he began to be a mighty one in the earth. He was a mighty hunter before

13:22.520 --> 13:30.360
the Lord, wherefore it is said, even as Nimrod the mighty hunter before the Lord. And the

13:30.360 --> 13:36.860
beginning of his kingdom was Babel, and Urek, and Akkad, and Calni, in the land of Shinar.

13:38.040 --> 13:45.220
Out of that land went forth Asher, and builded Nineveh, and the city Rehoboth, and Cala,

13:45.520 --> 13:49.980
and Rezin, between Nineveh and Cala, the same as a great city.

13:51.300 --> 13:58.830
And Misraim begat Ludim, and Adimim, and Lahabim, and Naphtihim, and Pathrasim, and Chazlehim,

13:59.680 --> 14:02.700
out of whom came Philistim, and Kaftorim.

14:03.500 --> 14:10.300
And Canaan begat Sidon his first born, and Heth, and the Jebusite, and the Amorite, and

14:10.300 --> 14:16.640
the Gergosite, and the Hivite, and the Arkite, and the Sinite, and the Arvidite, and the

14:16.640 --> 14:22.200
Zemurite, and the Haemothite. And afterward were the families of the Canaanites spread

14:22.200 --> 14:22.700
abroad.

14:24.280 --> 14:29.600
And the border of the Canaanites was from Sidon as thou comest to Girar, unto Gaza,

14:30.060 --> 14:38.040
as thou goest unto Sodom, and Gomorrah, and Adma, and Zeboam, even unto Lesha. These

14:38.040 --> 14:42.760
are the sons of Ham after their families, after their tongues, in their countries,

14:43.120 --> 14:44.320
and in their nations.

14:45.760 --> 14:51.400
Unto Shem also the father of all the children of Eber, the brother of Japheth the elder,

14:51.780 --> 14:59.240
even to him were children born. The children of Shem, Elam and Asher, and Arphaxad, and

14:59.240 --> 15:07.640
Lod, and Aram. And the children of Aram, Uz, and Hul, and Gether, and Mash. And Arphaxad

15:07.640 --> 15:14.740
begat Sala, and Sala begat Eber. And unto Eber were born two sons, the name of one was

15:14.740 --> 15:20.140
Peleg, for in his days was the earth divided, and his brother's name was Joktan.

15:21.720 --> 15:29.220
And Joktan begat El-Modad, and Shelef, and Hazar-Meveth, and Jira, and Hadorim, and Uzzal,

15:29.240 --> 15:37.960
and Dikla, and Obel, and Abimeel, and Sheba, and Ophir, and Havilah, and Jobab. All these

15:37.960 --> 15:43.960
were the sons of Joktan. And their dwelling was from Misha as thou goest unto Seafar,

15:44.320 --> 15:50.780
a mount of the east. These are the sons of Shem after their families, after their tongues,

15:51.040 --> 15:57.940
in their lands, after their nations. These are the families of the sons of Noah, after

15:57.940 --> 16:03.780
their generations, in their nations, and by these were the nations divided in the earth

16:03.780 --> 16:04.920
after the flood.

16:06.860 --> 16:07.980
CHAPTER XI

16:08.480 --> 16:14.560
And the whole earth was of one language and of one speech. And it came to pass, as they

16:14.560 --> 16:19.840
journeyed from the east, that they found a plain in the land of Shinar, and they dwelt

16:19.840 --> 16:26.880
there. And they said one to another, Go to, let us make brick, and burn them throughly.

16:27.200 --> 16:33.520
And they had brick for stone, and slime had they for mortar. And they said, Go to, let

16:33.520 --> 16:39.620
us build us a city and a tower, whose top may reach unto heaven, and let us make us

16:39.620 --> 16:43.880
a name, lest we be scattered abroad upon the face of the whole earth.

16:44.800 --> 16:50.520
And the Lord came down to see the city and the tower which the children of men builded.

16:50.520 --> 16:57.320
And the Lord said, Behold, the people is one, and they have all one language, and this they

16:57.320 --> 17:03.200
begin to do, and now nothing will be restrained from them which they have imagined to do.

17:04.120 --> 17:09.800
Go to, let us go down, and there confound their language, that they may not understand

17:09.800 --> 17:15.960
one another's speech. So the Lord scattered them abroad from thence upon the face of all

17:15.960 --> 17:22.540
the earth, and they left off to build the city. Therefore is the name of it called Babel,

17:22.780 --> 17:28.180
because the Lord did there confound the language of all the earth, and from thence did the

17:28.180 --> 17:31.620
Lord scatter them abroad upon the face of all the earth.

17:33.020 --> 17:39.180
These are the generations of Shem. Shem was an hundred years old, and begat Arphaxid two

17:39.180 --> 17:45.500
years after the flood. And Shem lived after he begat Arphaxid five hundred years, and

17:45.500 --> 17:52.980
begat sons and daughters. And Arphaxid lived five and thirty years, and begat Sala. And

17:52.980 --> 17:59.320
Arphaxid lived after he begat Sala four hundred and three years, and begat sons and daughters.

18:00.260 --> 18:07.180
And Sala lived thirty years, and begat Ybar. And Sala lived after he begat Ybar four hundred

18:07.180 --> 18:13.980
and three years, and begat sons and daughters. And Ybar lived four and thirty years, and

18:13.980 --> 18:18.900
begat Peleg. And Eber lived after he begat Peleg four hundred and

18:18.900 --> 18:24.200
thirty years, and begat sons and daughters. And Peleg lived thirty

18:24.200 --> 18:30.040
years, and begat Riou. And Peleg lived after he begat Riou two hundred

18:30.040 --> 18:35.620
and nine years, and begat sons and daughters. And Riou lived two and

18:35.620 --> 18:41.040
thirty years, and begat Siirog. And Riou lived after he begat Siirog

18:41.040 --> 18:44.920
two hundred and seven years, and begat sons and daughters.

18:46.000 --> 18:49.360
And Si-ragh lived thirty years, and begat Nahor.

18:49.980 --> 18:55.260
And Si-ragh lived after he begat Nahor, two hundred years, and begat sons

18:55.260 --> 18:56.040
and daughters.

18:56.980 --> 19:00.820
And Nahor lived nine and twenty years, and begat Terah.

19:01.340 --> 19:05.980
And Nahor lived after he begat Terah, and a hundred and nineteen years,

19:06.240 --> 19:08.160
and begat sons and daughters.

19:08.900 --> 19:14.140
And Tyra lived seventy years, and begat Abram, Nahor, and Haran.

19:15.680 --> 19:22.640
Now these are the generations of Tyra. Tyra begat Abram, Nahor, and Haran, and Haran begat

19:22.640 --> 19:30.220
Lot. And Haran died before his father Tyra in the land of his nativity in Ur of the Chaldees.

19:31.300 --> 19:37.480
And Abram and Nahor took them wives. The name of Abram's wife was Sarai, and the name of

19:37.480 --> 19:43.660
Nahor's wife, Milka, the daughter of Haran, the father of Milka, and the father of Iska.

19:44.600 --> 19:51.880
But Sarai was barren, she had no child. And Tyra took Abram his son, and Lot the son of

19:51.880 --> 19:58.740
Haran his son's son, and Sarai his daughter-in-law, his son Abram's wife, and they went forth

19:58.740 --> 20:04.660
with them from Ur of the Chaldees to go into the land of Canaan, and they came unto Haran

20:04.660 --> 20:11.600
and dwelt there. And the days of Tyra were two hundred and five years, and Tyra died

20:11.600 --> 20:12.640
in Haran.

20:14.380 --> 20:15.420
Chapter 12

20:15.420 --> 20:21.320
Now the LORD had said unto Abram, Get thee out of thy country, and from thy kindred,

20:21.640 --> 20:27.240
and from thy father's house, unto a land that I will show thee. And I will make of thee

20:27.240 --> 20:33.100
a great nation, and I will bless thee, and make thy name great, and thou shalt be a blessing.

20:33.620 --> 20:39.640
And I will bless them that bless thee, and curse him that curseth thee, and in thee shall

20:39.640 --> 20:41.900
all families of the earth be blessed.

20:43.620 --> 20:49.920
So Abram departed as the LORD had spoken unto him, and Lot went with him, and Abram was

20:49.920 --> 20:56.820
seventy and five years old when he departed out of Haran. And Abram took Sarai his wife,

20:57.200 --> 21:02.420
and Lot his brother's son, and all their substance that they had gathered, and the souls that

21:02.420 --> 21:08.160
they had gotten in Haran, and they went forth to go into the land of Canaan, and into the

21:08.160 --> 21:09.960
land of Canaan they came.

21:11.260 --> 21:17.760
And Abram passed through the land unto the place of Sycam, unto the plain of Moray, and

21:17.760 --> 21:24.540
the Canaanite was then in the land. And the LORD appeared unto Abram, and said, Unto thy

21:24.540 --> 21:31.080
seed will I give this land, and their ability an altar unto the LORD who appeared unto him.

21:31.740 --> 21:37.180
And he removed from thence unto a mountain on the east of Bethel, and pitched his tent,

21:37.660 --> 21:43.460
having Bethel on the west, and Haei on the east, and there he builded an altar unto the

21:43.460 --> 21:50.260
LORD, and called upon the name of the LORD. And Abram journeyed, going on still toward

21:50.260 --> 21:51.020
the south.

21:52.640 --> 21:58.260
And there was a famine in the land, and Abram went down into Egypt to sojourn there, for

21:58.260 --> 22:03.960
the famine was grievous in the land. And it came to pass, when he was come near to

22:03.960 --> 22:10.300
enter into Egypt, that he said unto Sarai his wife, Behold now, I know that thou art

22:10.300 --> 22:16.280
a fair woman to look upon. Therefore it shall come to pass, when the Egyptians shall see

22:16.280 --> 22:21.900
thee, that they shall say, This is his wife, and they will kill me, but they will save

22:21.900 --> 22:22.860
thee alive.

22:23.840 --> 22:30.480
Say, I pray thee, thou art my sister, that it may be well with me for thy sake, and my

22:30.480 --> 22:32.540
soul shall live because of thee.

22:33.700 --> 22:39.520
And it came to pass, that, when Abram was come into Egypt, the Egyptians beheld the

22:39.520 --> 22:46.140
woman, that she was very fair. The princes also of Pharaoh saw her, and commended her

22:46.140 --> 22:52.960
before Pharaoh, and the woman was taken into Pharaoh's house. And he entreated Abram well

22:52.960 --> 22:59.820
for her sake, and he had sheep, and oxen, and he-asses, and men-servants, and maid-servants,

23:00.060 --> 23:07.160
and she-asses, and camels. And the LORD plagued Pharaoh and his house with great plagues because

23:07.160 --> 23:14.320
of Sarai, Abram's wife. And Pharaoh called Abram, and said, What is this that thou hast

23:14.320 --> 23:20.880
done unto me? Why didst thou not tell me that she was thy wife? Why saidst thou, She is

